        • [ - ] Ideas - member since 15-Feb-17

          Just to add. Ozil should never play against top sides for a reason. He's only good if his side are dominating possession. If the other side has more of the ball he's weak without possession but he also isn't the type of player you want for counter attacking football. His set piece also tend to be worse if he's had less touches and his team isn't dominating. Doesn't help on defensive set pieces and often runs into dead ends with the ball. He's basically pointless against good sides. If I was Arsenal manager I'd only ever use Ozil against the weaker sides (and he is very effective against weaker sides). Against the stronger sides (good or great ones) I'd leave Ozil out always. The most alarming thing here for me out of everything is that Wenger thought Iwobi was appropriate in an away game against Bayern.

          Gabriel came on and although Mustafi should've done more to prevent Lewa getting that nice a contact, it was as I said below a perfect cross and excellent header, Gabriel was 100% at fault for Thiago's first. Anything 3-1 or above then Bayern will be under minimal pressure in the return leg. Hopefully Lucas or Welbeck start ahead of Iwobi, preferably Welbeck so we still have pace but more of a goal threat (and end product in general). Alexis starting in the 9 ahead of Giroud should at least get Hummels and Martinez moving around and they will defend fairly high being at home. Hope nobody has a Gabriel moment either. I predict 2-1 Bayern, mixture of head and heart.
